Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:07.500
Authentic Baba Ghanoush Recipe

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:13.500
Preparation: 15 min. - Cooking: 45 min.

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:16.000
Serves: 4

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Ingredients

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:22.000
500 g aubergines

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
6 tbsp tahini (sesame paste)

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.500
1 red bell pepper, deseeded and finely chopped

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:36.500
1 red green pepper, deseeded and finely chopped

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:39.000
3 green onions, finely chopped

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.000
2 cloves of garlic, crushed

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.800
Salt to taste

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:49.000
1 tbsp pomegranate seeds

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:53.000
1 tbsp pomegranate molasses

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:58.000
1 tbsp chopped walnuts

00:00:58.000 --> 00:00:59.000
Olive oil

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:05.000
Directions

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Preheat the oven to 210Â°C.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:22.000
Prick the aubergines with a fork and bake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:37.000
Peel the skin off the aubergines as soon as they come out of the oven

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:45.000
Place the aubergines in a sieve placed over a bowl to cool and drain in the fridge.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:51.000
Once cool, finely chop the aubergines with a knife.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:02:11.000
Add the red and green peppers to the aubergines along with onions and garlic then season with salt to taste and finally add the tahini and stir well.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Garnish with the walnuts, pomegranate molasses and pomegranate seeds then drizzle the olive oil over. Serve with Arabic flat bread.

